<h1>Problem 221 - Tournament of Towns 2008, Senior A-level Q7</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 6</h2>
<p>A test consists of \(30\) true or false questions. After the test (answering all \(30\) questions), Victor gets his score: the number of correct answers. Victor is allowed to take the test (the same questions ) several times. Can Victor work out a strategy that insure him to get a perfect score after
<ul><li> \(30\)th attempt?</li>
<li> \(25\)th attempt?</li></ul>
(Initially, Victor does not know any answer)</p>
